relationships with her neighbors then everyone else in the region (one
day I'd love to find out how much Jordan and Israel have really
cooperated for instance), but that the dynamics of the whole region is
very different of the Arab world gets a little richer then it did and
Israel develops a little slower. One would assume deeper involvement
in the non-aligned movement might do that. Of course I might be off a
bit (i.e. involvement in these things has no substantive effect on
Israeli economic policy, a richer Arab world just buys bigger guns
etc.) and certainly I don't have insight into Middle Eastern Economic
development.
